Five sample summaries

[1] He was elected mayor of Caracas, the capital of Venezuela, in 2000. When he ran for high office in 2008, he was barred from running and was jailed for campaigning. Venezuela, where he lives, is an autocracy, and he has always had doubts about it. Ten years ago, 3.1 billion people were living under autocratic rule. This is about 42% of the world's population. Meanwhile, approximately 5.7 billion people, or approximately 72% of the world's population, currently live under autocratic rule. There are 5.7 billion people who cannot live freely. I have three opinions on what should be done to improve this situation. The first is that we must not allow dictators to become legitimized. The second is to support democracy and carry out freedom movements. The third is to create a global movement. We should be as networking about issues of democracy as we are about climate change.
[2] 150 In the video, he was talking about the importance of freedom through his experience or background. He strongly believed that if we cannot live in a democratic society, we cannot get freedom. When he was in prison, he made own rules, and one of them was reading books. He read more and more about the hero's lives. Then he was inspired by them. Then he thought that he had to move to win the democracy. To defeat autocracies, he said we need to make a network with them. Also, we have to make a movement. Now , 72% of the world 's people are under a society of autocratic rule. If the trend keeps going, after 25 years, in 2050, the entire world will be autocratic. Therefore we take action as soon as possible. He suggested three kinds of action or movement. Lastly he said we need to speak out, and win democracy.                                                              
[3] Lopez talks about freedom and democracy. The history of Venezuela is one of military rule, exile, imprisonment and politics. When he was in prison, he thought about what freedom and democracy meant. In fact, freedom is about the possibility of doing many things . You can not have freedom without democracy. You can not have democracy if people are not free. Only 10 years ago, 42 percent of the world population was living under autocratic rule. Today, 72 percent of the global population is living under autocratic rule. Then, people from different backgrounds spoke about what it meant to fight for freedom and to comfort the autocratic. If you care about some social problem, you need to concerned about the rise of autocracy and the need or democracy.                                                                                                                            
[4]                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
[5] To make freedom and democracy, we need to be concerned about autocracy and create a movement for this. Leopoldo Lopez said that people must take the following three actions. First of all, we need to stop legitimizing autocrats. Autocracy is currently comfortable to do business with the government, but we have to think about smart sanctions. Second, there needs to be support for the people and democracy movements. Providing Internet access to people all over the world and using new technology such as bitcoin will support pro-democracy movements. Finally, we need to build a global movement for freedom and democracy. To achieve freedom and democracy, it is important to take action.
